win in France, or Arshile Gorky in New York City, Balakian’s layered, elliptical language, wired phrases, and shifting tempos engage both life’s harshness and beauty and define his inventive and distinctive style.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2022) 0aAmerican poetryy21st century. 7aPOETRY / General.2bisacsh  aamerican poetry, creative writing, phoenix poets series, political realities, social issues, planetary transmutation, mass violence, culture, long-form poems, collections, new jersey palisades, dialogue, memory, geological history, climate crisis, hiroshima mon amour, vietnam war, george washington bridge, power of love, sensuality, meditations, trauma, atrocities.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Complete eBook-Package 2022z978311076650940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226784106423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226784106/original  a978-3-11-076650-9  University of Chicago Complete eBook-Package 2022b2022  aGBV-deGruyter-alles